Title: Object: Iter Jacobi in Egyptum
Series: Knowsley Gallery
Description: Jacob standing in front of a pair of oxen on the right, holding a staff and looking up to left, following God's command to take his family and go into Egypt; two boys feeding goats, sheep and leading a donkey, beside him and a figure riding a donkey into the distance in the background; after Jacopo Bassano. 1728 Etching
Associated names: Associated with: James Stanley, 10th Earl of Derby
